                    <head>Henricus de Frimaria, Quaestiones in quartum librum Sententiarum. Summa rudium</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="SL1" to="SL1" scheme="other"/>
                                            <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <material>Parchment</material>
                                        <note>
                                            <locus from="SL1" to="SL1" scheme="other"/> is the former pastedown which has been detached from the cover. <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> carries offprint from the pastedown. <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/> is also loose and it is possible to lift it and look the text on the verso as well as the board underneath.</note>
                                        <dimensions type="leaf">
                                            <height quantity="210" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="145" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" quantity="1" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. <secFol>Item ibi sunt </secFol>
                                </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1(14), 2(10), 3-8(12), 9(14), 10-13(12), 14(10, lacks 9-10)), 15-17(12), 18(8)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/682724edf060c60001cc192a/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. Parchment guards made from strips of an old manuscript.</p>
                                    <signatures>Two sets of quire signatures in Arabic numerals; the first visible at the first leaves of quires 5-9, the second on quire 12-13.</signatures>
                                    <catchwords>Catchwords on quire 17. </catchwords>
                                </collation>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="unknown">
                                <p> Medieval binding. Originally, leather over bevelled wooden boards. 3 double raised bands and endbands. Originally, corner and centre bosses. Catchplate and strap attachment plate of brass. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, two damaged labels, the first one illegible; the second has what looks like <quote>273</quote> written in red ink.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="SL1" to="SL1" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>: the detached pastedowns consist of fragments in a pregothic script from Honorius Augustodunensis's Speculum ecclesiae (<locus from="SL1vb" to="SL1vb" scheme="folios"/> paragraph beginning with <quote>PAVLUS</quote> see <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">PL</title>
                                        <citedRange from="172" to="172" unit="volume"/>
                                        <citedRange from="974" to="974" unit="column"/>
                                    </bibl>).</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="210" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="150" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="65" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather almost completely removed, only minute pieces remain. Holes on <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/> after bosses. Straps missing. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, the lables seem to have been reattached directly on the bookblock after the leather was removed. Board attachement visible on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>. Both covers carry signs of bookworms, <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/> is especially affected.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100104">Germany</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100311">Bavaria</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate when="1406">1406</origDate> and <origDate when="1427">1427</origDate>. The colophon on <locus from="109va" to="109va" scheme="folios"/> states that the text was finished in <date when="1406"/> and the colophon for the second part on <locus from="208v" to="208v" scheme="folios"/> gives the year <date when="1427"/>. In addition, at the bottom of <locus from="111r" to="111r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <date when="1405"/> is written. The second colophon also gives the name of the author, <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102696">Master Joahnnes from Neuburg</persName> (probably <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100325">Neuburg an der Donau</placeName>).</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>According to the addition on <locus from="208v" to="208v" scheme="folios"/> the manuscript was given to the<orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100157"> Carthusian monastery in Buxheim</orgName> in <date when="1435"/> by Master Johannes (the same year he died). The manuscript probably remained at the monastery library until the monastery was dissolved in <date when="1802"/>. However, on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="166v" to="166v" scheme="folios"/> there are some short additions by a medieval hand in French, which indicates that the manuscript has either travelled or that a French speaker has travelled to the manuscript.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Purchased by the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100181">Stockholm City Book Auction (Stockholms stads bokauktionskammare)</orgName> in <date when="1956"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
