                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1ra" to="109va" scheme="folios"/>Cursiva antiquior. </handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="111ra" to="166vb" scheme="folios"/>Cursiva antiquior.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top left corner, in ink by a medieval hand (perhaps the scribe): <quote>? Summa Rudium et scriptis/scripture super? 4 sentenciarum</quote>; below, by an early modern hand: <quote>Cartusiae in Buxheim</quote>; inside the initial Q, by a medieval hand: <quote>gloriouse mere dieu</quote>; bottom of page: two National Library stamps (one smudged), in blue ink: <quote>1956/5</quote> (accession number), in black ink by an early modern hand: <quote>N 101</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1v" to="109r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal adiditions by the scribe or a contemporary hands. The additions consist mainly of short corrections, the abbreviation for <quote>dubitatur</quote> (also found in the text) seems to be used as a keyword, and a type of rubric written in the bottom margin and keyed to the text with a signe-de-renovoi, e.g. on <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="111r" to="111r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page in brown ink by a medieval hand (the scribe?):<quote> In nomine domini</quote>; bottom of page:<quote> 1405</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="111r" to="166v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Short additions in the margin by at least one medieval hand, most often keywords, e.g. <locus from="112r" to="112r" scheme="folios"/>, but in places some type of commentary has been written in a faint brown ink, e.g. on <locus from="115v" to="115v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="166v" to="166v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>After the main text a medieval hand has written two lines in French.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1ra" to="1ra" scheme="folios"/>: Opening initial Q over 12 lines outlined in red ink. <locus from="2rb" to="109ra" scheme="folios"/>: on <locus from="2rb" to="2rb" scheme="folios"/> a plain iniital over 3 lines outlined in red ink, from <locus from="3vb" to="3vb" scheme="folios"/> only space reserved for intials. <locus from="111ra" to="111ra" scheme="folios"/>: text opened by a plain initial over 4 lines in red. <locus from="112rb" to="165ra" scheme="folios"/>: space (3 lines) reserved for initials.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="edges">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="Tail" to="Tail" scheme="other"/>, brown ink in a red frame: <quote>Summa rudium et super 4 sentenciarum</quote>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
                    </msPart>
                    <msPart>
                        <msIdentifier>
                            <idno type="codicologicalUnit">2</idno>
                        </msIdentifier>
                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="167r" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Summa rudium</title>
                                <incipit>
                                    <supplied reason="omitted">Q</supplied>via varia dicta sanctorum et contrarie oppiniones diuersorum doctorum legentibus complexitates </incipit>
                                <explicit>cum intencione legatur et cetera</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Et sic terminatur summa Rudium autentica ad honorem gloriose virginis marie Et beati dominici patris nostri ordinis fratrum predicatorum et ad perfectum simplicium sacerdotum prestante domino nostro ihesu christo qui vnus est deus cum patre et <add place="above">sancto</add> spiritu per omnia benedictus amen </finalRubric>
                                <note>The Summa rudium was printed by <ref target="https://archive.org/details/jbc.bj.uj.edu.pl.NDIGSTDR049378/page/n3/mode/2up">Johann Otmar in 1487</ref>.</note>
                                <colophon>
                                    <locus from="208v" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>hec summula Rudium autentica conscripta a me iohanne magistro? de n<add place="above">e</add>uburg finita est Sub anno domini milesimo 1427 ? octo dies ? festum <add place="above">beati</add> iacobi maiorum hora vesperarum et cetera et cetera deo gracias requiescat in pace amen Non bene scribo sed melius discere volo Amen </colophon>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="paper">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="167" to="210" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Paper</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="210" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="145" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                            <watermark n="1">
                                                <locusGrp>
                                                    <locus from="167" to="208" scheme="folios"/>
                                                </locusGrp>
                                                <term type="watermarkMotif">Oxhead with horns turned outward, above single line rod ending with a star </term>
                                                <note>Possibly similar to Piccard II:2, X, 711-717 (only upper part of motif visible).</note>
                                            </watermark>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="44" unit="folios"/>
