                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-4">
                                    <locus from="167r" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>Gothic cursive.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="167r" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Additions and corrections in the margin by at least two medieval hands. Most additions are short, corrections or keywords, but others are more substantial, e.g. on <locus from="184v" to="184v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="196r" to="196r" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="208v" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Bottom of page, in brown ink by a medieval hand: <quote>hic liber est carthusiensium domus aule marie in buchshain prope memmingen augustiensis diocesis quem dedit eis magister Iohannes plebanus in nuburg anno domini 1435 in quo et obiit circa aprilem oretur pro eo requiescat in pace amen</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
